
---

### 2. `.gitignore`
This file tells Git to ignore certain files (junk files, system files, or sensitive keys) that shouldn't be uploaded to GitHub.

Create a file named `.gitignore` (no file extension) in your main folder:

```gitignore
# OS generated files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db

# Dependency directories (if you use npm/node later)
node_modules/

# Build artifacts
*.zip

# Private keys (CRITICAL: Never upload your .pem key)
*.pem

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
